{
  "stem": "1338.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So as I was alluding to the dichotomy that my father would have between the religious or national-- probably, I would call it national upbringing, Jewish National upbringing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it's obviously, not having a nation-- at least in the normal sense-- that was always the glue that kept it together, it was religion.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So needless to say, he had to have that element too, and insisted on it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so, when I was bar mitzvahed, I had a tutor, despite the fact that I spoke Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had a tutor for the particular thing that you have to do to learn during the prayer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I have-- and my father, by connections, probably-- friends or whatever-- actually insisted it be done in an orthodox temple-- synagogue, very orthodox.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I read whatever, you know?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And those of you who are familiar, it is called the Haftarah, which you read the whole thing, and the prayers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had, obviously, no difficulty in my-- in the language, itself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it wasn't the same thing as probably here, where you have to, through the bar mitzvah, you have to also learn the language.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "For me, it was the natural language which I could speak.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I did go through it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, then I-- and it was a natural and acquired part of my life in the school, because every kid, at that time, my classmate, had bar mitzvah in the seventh grade.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So needless to say, I wasn't going to be deprived of that either, even if my father didn't care to have it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I had that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After that, my aunt-- because we didn't have an apartment any more-- my aunt actually threw a party.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
